Limits and trade-offs of AI in content marketing
AI is not a replacement for human judgment. It excels at pattern recognition, scale, and optimization. It struggles with nuance, originality, and ethical considerations without guidance. Content that relies solely on automation risks sounding generic and losing credibility.

The most effective strategies combine AI insights with human expertise. Editorial oversight, industry knowledge, and strategic thinking remain essential. AI supports execution, but humans own perspective. 

